The paper addresses the problem of visual quality of images reconstructed from block-wise random projections, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves modifying the sensing and reconstruction process, which involves signal processing and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of a fast preview for the purpose of prediction, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM). The enforcement of smoothness across block borders can also be considered a graphics problem (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of PSNR and SSIM index to assess quality, which are common metrics in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
